<div class="container">
<header>
  <a href="../index.html" title="Zurück zum Englisch-Lernzentrum" style="display:inline-block;text-decoration:none">
    <img src="../assets/logo_hellweg.png" alt="Logo der Hellweg-Realschule Unna-Massen" style="cursor:pointer"/>
  </a>
  <h1>to be (am / is / are)</h1>
  <p class="sub">Klasse 5 – Unit 1</p>
</header>

<section class="rules-combined">
<h2>Regelkarten</h2>
<div class="rc-grid">

<div class="rc-card c-amber">
<div class="rc-card-body">
<div class="rc-card-label">Was bedeutet „to be"?</div>
<div class="rc-card-num">1</div>
<div class="rc-zone-core">„To be" bedeutet <b>sein</b> oder <b>sich befinden</b>. Es sagt, <b>wer</b>, <b>wie</b> oder <b>wo</b> jemand oder etwas ist.</div>
<div class="rc-zone-table">
<div class="rc-zone-table-title">Drei Verwendungen</div>
<ul class="rc-detail-list">
<li><b>Wer/Was?</b> – I <span class="hl-accent">am</span> Tom.</li>
<li><b>Wie?</b> – She <span class="hl-accent">is</span> happy.</li>
<li><b>Wo?</b> – They <span class="hl-accent">are</span> in the classroom.</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="rc-zone-examples">
<span class="rc-zone-examples-icon">📝</span>
<span class="rc-zone-examples-body">
<span class="ex-line">I <span class="hl-accent">am</span> Tom. <span class="ex-de">– Ich heiße Tom.</span></span>
<span class="ex-line">She <span class="hl-accent">is</span> happy. <span class="ex-de">– Sie ist glücklich.</span></span>
<span class="ex-line">They <span class="hl-accent">are</span> in school. <span class="ex-de">– Sie sind in der Schule.</span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<div class="rc-card c-green">
<div class="rc-card-body">
<div class="rc-card-label">✅ Aussagesatz</div>
<div class="rc-card-num">2</div>
<div class="rc-zone-core">Jedes Pronomen hat seine eigene Form von „to be": <b>am · is · are</b>.</div>
<div class="rc-zone-table">
<div class="rc-zone-table-title">Pronomen + Form</div>
<table class="rc-table-pron">
<thead><tr><th>Pronomen</th><th>Form</th><th>Deutsch</th></tr></thead>
<tbody>
<tr><td>I</td><td>am</td><td>ich bin</td></tr>
<tr><td>you</td><td>are</td><td>du bist</td></tr>
<tr><td>he</td><td>is</td><td>er ist</td></tr>
<tr><td>she</td><td>is</td><td>sie ist</td></tr>
<tr><td>it</td><td>is</td><td>es ist</td></tr>
<tr><td>we</td><td>are</td><td>wir sind</td></tr>
<tr class="is-plural"><td>you</td><td>are</td><td>ihr seid</td></tr>
<tr><td>they</td><td>are</td><td>sie sind</td></tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<div class="rc-zone-examples">
<span class="rc-zone-examples-icon">📝</span>
<span class="rc-zone-examples-body">
<span class="ex-line">I <span class="hl-accent">am</span> ten years old.</span>
<span class="ex-line">He <span class="hl-accent">is</span> from England.</span>
<span class="ex-line">We <span class="hl-accent">are</span> in the classroom.</span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<div class="rc-card c-teal">
<div class="rc-card-body">
<div class="rc-card-label">Kurzformen (Contractions)</div>
<div class="rc-card-num">3</div>
<div class="rc-zone-core">Pronomen + „to be" werden oft <b>zusammengezogen</b>. Das ist gesprochenes Englisch.</div>
<div class="rc-zone-table">
<div class="rc-zone-table-title">Lang → Kurz</div>
<table class="rc-table-pron">
<thead><tr><th>Pronomen</th><th>Kurzform</th><th>Lang</th></tr></thead>
<tbody>
<tr><td>I</td><td>I'm</td><td>I am</td></tr>
<tr><td>you</td><td>you're</td><td>you are</td></tr>
<tr><td>he</td><td>he's</td><td>he is</td></tr>
<tr><td>she</td><td>she's</td><td>she is</td></tr>
<tr><td>it</td><td>it's</td><td>it is</td></tr>
<tr><td>we</td><td>we're</td><td>we are</td></tr>
<tr class="is-plural"><td>you</td><td>you're</td><td>you are</td></tr>
<tr><td>they</td><td>they're</td><td>they are</td></tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<div class="rc-zone-examples">
<span class="rc-zone-examples-icon">📝</span>
<span class="rc-zone-examples-body">
<span class="ex-line"><span class="hl-accent">I'm</span> happy. <span class="ex-de">(statt „I am happy")</span></span>
<span class="ex-line"><span class="hl-accent">She's</span> my friend. <span class="ex-de">(statt „She is my friend")</span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<div class="rc-card c-red">
<div class="rc-card-body">
<div class="rc-card-label">❌ Verneinung</div>
<div class="rc-card-num">4</div>
<div class="rc-zone-core">Für „nicht sein" hängst du <b>not</b> hinter die Form von „to be": <b>am not / is not / are not</b>.</div>
<div class="rc-zone-table">
<div class="rc-zone-table-title">Pronomen + Verneinung</div>
<table class="rc-table-pron">
<thead><tr><th>Pronomen</th><th>Verneinung</th><th>Kurzform</th></tr></thead>
<tbody>
<tr><td>I</td><td>am not</td><td>I'm not</td></tr>
<tr><td>you</td><td>are not</td><td>aren't</td></tr>
<tr><td>he</td><td>is not</td><td>isn't</td></tr>
<tr><td>she</td><td>is not</td><td>isn't</td></tr>
<tr><td>it</td><td>is not</td><td>isn't</td></tr>
<tr><td>we</td><td>are not</td><td>aren't</td></tr>
<tr class="is-plural"><td>you</td><td>are not</td><td>aren't</td></tr>
<tr><td>they</td><td>are not</td><td>aren't</td></tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<div class="rc-zone-examples">
<span class="rc-zone-examples-icon">📝</span>
<span class="rc-zone-examples-body">
<span class="ex-line"><span class="hl-accent-error">I'm not</span> sad. <span class="ex-de">– Ich bin nicht traurig.</span></span>
<span class="ex-line">She <span class="hl-accent-error">isn't</span> from Germany. <span class="ex-de">– Sie ist nicht aus Deutschland.</span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<div class="rc-card c-blue">
<div class="rc-card-body">
<div class="rc-card-label">❓ Ja/Nein-Frage</div>
<div class="rc-card-num">5</div>
<div class="rc-zone-core">Bei der Frage <b>tauschst du Pronomen und Form</b>. Die Form von „to be" kommt nach vorne.</div>
<div class="rc-zone-table">
<div class="rc-zone-table-title">Frageform</div>
<ul class="rc-detail-list">
<li><span class="hl-accent-info">Am</span> I happy?</li>
<li><span class="hl-accent-info">Are</span> you from England?</li>
<li><span class="hl-accent-info">Is</span> he ten?</li>
<li><span class="hl-accent-info">Is</span> she your sister?</li>
<li><span class="hl-accent-info">Is</span> it a cat?</li>
<li><span class="hl-accent-info">Are</span> we late?</li>
<li><span class="hl-accent-info">Are</span> you (Pl.) ready?</li>
<li><span class="hl-accent-info">Are</span> they your friends?</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="rc-zone-examples">
<span class="rc-zone-examples-icon">📝</span>
<span class="rc-zone-examples-body">
<span class="ex-line"><span class="hl-accent-info">Are</span> you tired? <span class="ex-de">– Bist du müde?</span></span>
<span class="ex-line"><span class="hl-accent-info">Is</span> Tom your brother? <span class="ex-de">– Ist Tom dein Bruder?</span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<div class="rc-card c-indigo">
<div class="rc-card-body">
<div class="rc-card-label">Kurzantworten</div>
<div class="rc-card-num">6</div>
<div class="rc-zone-core">Bei Fragen antwortest du mit dem <b>Pronomen + Form von „to be"</b>. Das Hauptverb wird <b>nicht wiederholt</b>.</div>
<div class="rc-zone-table">
<div class="rc-zone-table-title">Frage → Antwort</div>
<ul class="rc-detail-list">
<li><span class="qa-q">Are you happy?</span><br><span class="qa-a">Yes, I <span class="hl-accent-info">am</span>. / No, I'm <span class="hl-accent-error">not</span>.</span></li>
<li><span class="qa-q">Is he from England?</span><br><span class="qa-a">Yes, he <span class="hl-accent-info">is</span>. / No, he <span class="hl-accent-error">isn't</span>.</span></li>
<li><span class="qa-q">Are they in school?</span><br><span class="qa-a">Yes, they <span class="hl-accent-info">are</span>. / No, they <span class="hl-accent-error">aren't</span>.</span></li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="rc-zone-examples">
